
Day 9 (part two,  high-level languages )

Advantages of High-level languages.
- Programs are easily portable between computers of different makes

- Programs are easy to modify, and also to incorporate additional features thus enhancing its functional capabilities.
- They enable programmers to adapt easily to new hardware.  This is because; the programmer doesnâ€™t need to worry about the hardware design of the computer.

- They are easy to debug (remove errors), and maintain.

Disadvantages of High-level languages
- They are not machine-oriented; hence, do not use of the CPU and hardware facilities efficiently

- Need to be interpreted or compiled to machine-readable form before the computer can execute them.

Commonly used high-level languages are: 
 ~ Python, javascript, java, C++, C# etc.